1. Reconnaissance - Research, identify, select targets
2. Weaponization - Pair remote access malware into a payload
3. Delivery - Transmit to target (email attachment, usb drives, phishing)
4. Exploitation - Once it is delivered, how is the weapon triggered
5. Installation - The weapon installs a backdoor to maintain persistance
6. Command & Control - How the computer communicates with the attackers server
7. Actions on Objective - How the attacker achieves their goal.
